Laparoscopic evaluation of small pelvic adhesions in female patients treated for infertility. The range and nature of adhesions found out by means of laparoscopy was analysed in patients diagnosed because of infertility. 38% of patients had laparotomy performed previously. Adhesions concerned 47% of the reproductive organ, although in nearly the same percentage intestine and greater omentum were involved. In 13 (31%) patients occurrence of endometriosis focus was discovered. In the area of Fallopian tube--ovary there were most often non-vascularized, thin adhesions and solid adhesions in the area of Douglas sinus.